node.text:
Prepare yourselves... @whatsthomaseating and I challenged each other to a blind taste test of the new @edys @dreyers Rocky Road Collection and honestly, I've never loved my job more!! Take a wild guess who has the better palate.... #ad

If you're down to get crazy and try all the insanely delish flavors, THIS IS YOUR MOMENT. Now through Wednesday, June 9, buy just one full-size flavor from the EDY'S or Dreyer’s recently launched and get the rest of the collection for free when you share a photo of your ice cream on Instagram. Details on how to enter are below! Which flavor would you try first?

🍦 Purchase one of the six Rocky Road Collection flavors at a national grocery retailer near you. Mocha Almond Avenue, Brownie Brick Road, Cookie Cobblestone, Chocolate Peanut Butter Park, Salted Caramel Pretzel Path and/or The Original Rocky Road
🍦 Share a photo of your purchase on Instagram via an in-feed post or Instagram story using the #NationalRockyRoadDay. Can’t make it to the store? No problem! Just comment on @edys or @dreyers promotion post using #NationalRockyRoadDay with one sentence about which flavor of the Rocky Road Collection you’re most excited to try and why.
🍦 Make sure you’re following @edys and @dreyers and tag the handles in your post. Don’t forget to set your profile to Public so they can see your entry!
🍦 EDY'S (Dreyer's) will direct message eligible entrants while supplies last with next steps on how to claim their free ice cream!
NO PURCHASE NECESSARY. Limit to one entry per person. Open to legal residents of the 50 United States (D.C), 13 and older. Entries must be received by 11:59pm PDT on 6/9/21. For Official Rules, go to the link in the @edys @dreyers bio.

Get ready for your new fav meatless Monday dinner that also happens to be ready in LESS than 20 minutes Riced Cauliflower Veggie Burrito Bowls!! #ad 

We’re taking a little helping hand from @birdseyevegetables to get that fresh taste no matter what time of year you make these! Watch the video for all the steps, or grab the printable recipe on my website. Don’t skimp on the guac if you know what’s good for you. And yes, feel free to add chicken or steak or fish… that riced cauliflower is the perfect base! https://whatsgabycooking.com/cauliflower-rice-veggie-burrito-bowl/

node.text:
That’s a wrap on this week, happy hour starts now! Sipping on this incredible summery Blackberry Margarita, kicking my feet up and calling it a day! Make this for yourself this weekend, you’ll be obsessed! Snag a bottle of @Cointreau_US (it makes all margaritas better), your fav tequila, and some blackberries and you’re in business. #CointreauCollective
 
1 ounce Cointreau 
2 ounces blanco tequila
1 ounce lime juice
8 blackberries, muddled
Sparkling water to finish
Limes to garnish
 
Muddle the blackberries in a cocktail shaker with a muddler or the end of a wooden spoon. Add the other liquids and stir to combine. Strain to remove most of the seeds. Serve over crushed ice.

node.text: 10000% fully obsessed with these Zucchini Fritters with Yogurt Feta Dipping sauce 💚 After visiting my parents a few weeks ago, I know that if you have a garden with zucchini, it’s go time. And if you don’t have a garden, and your neighbor is gifting you zucchini like there’s no tomorrow, it’s still go time. And even if neither of those is your reality… you know it’s coming out of all corners of the markets these days. So… grab a container of @stonyfield Organic Greek and make the most incredible yogurt dipping sauce, fry up some zucchini fritters, and then live your best life. Grab the recipe on the blog!! https://whatsgabycooking.com/zucchini-fritters-with-yogurt-feta-dipping-sauce/

node.text:
Let’s talk about finding BALANCE as a new parent. I feel like I’ve been a little MIA here the past few months. I’ve been trying to find my new groove being a mom, a wife, a business owner, a friend and somehow also finding a few mins every day for myself… it’s a LOT!! 

Pre-Poppy, I always prided myself on being super responsive (aka answering your DM’s within an hour in case you had a question mid-cooking), showing you how-to’s of recipes on the daily, taking you behind the scenes on shoots, etc. I miss being able to do that!! And while I know we’ll get back there one day, I also loooove my new role as a mama and try to be aware of how much time I’m spending on my phone while I’m with her as I want to be completely present. 

Anyways - moral of the story… balance is HARD WORK. And I’ve come to realize there’s no perfect formula that fits everyone. And just when you think you’ve got the hang of it, something changes and you pivot. And while I sit here and think about all that, I just want to say that I’m just super grateful for this WGC community. And I appreciate each and every one of you being here! And for everyone else out there trying to keep all the balls up in the air, I see you! Keep kicking ass. 🤍
